<airframe>

  <section name="IMU" prefix="IMU_">
    
    <define name="ACCEL_X_NEUTRAL" value="49"/>
    <define name="ACCEL_Y_NEUTRAL" value="-37"/>
    <define name="ACCEL_Z_NEUTRAL" value="19"/>
    <define name="ACCEL_X_SENS" value="2.4559027833652873" integer="16"/>
    <define name="ACCEL_Y_SENS" value="2.440276225201743" integer="16"/>
    <define name="ACCEL_Z_SENS" value="2.434614999778432" integer="16"/>

  </section>

</airframe>

<!-- 
Bebop2 IMU calibration:
ACCEL:
1 - Flash the board with your normal AP firmware (if it is not already on it.)
2 - Switch to the “raw sensors” telemetry mode in the GCS via Settings
3 - rotate bebop to all imaginary sides of a cube, and keep it still at every orientation for 10 seconds
4 - Stop the server so it will write the log file (to var/logs).
5 - run the script :
sw/tools/calibration/calibrate.py -s ACCEL -p var/logs/YY_MM_DD__hh_mm_ss.data
6 - add printed values to the airframe file or this file

MAG:
0 - This calibration can only be done outside, far away from metal objects
1 - Flash the board with your normal AP firmware (if it is not already on it.)
2 - Switch to the “raw sensors” telemetry mode in the GCS via Settings
3 - slowly spin bebop around all axis, in as much orientations as possible
4 - Stop the server so it will write the log file (to var/logs).
5 - run the script :
sw/tools/calibration/calibrate.py -s MAG -p var/logs/YY_MM_DD__hh_mm_ss.data
6 - add printed values to the airframe file or this file

-->
